				\begin{document}$$ RSD=\frac{\sqrt{\sigma }}{\mu } $$\end{document}RSD=σμ, where σ represented total variance and μ represented the mean (the constant from the regression output). Differences in variance between days and between months were estimated using likelihood ratio test comparing the full model with a model where day or month, respectively, was taken out of the model.
